Apple has released iOS 11.3 for its mobile device users. The update measures in at 708MB on an iPhone X, and packs a wide range of new features. Apple said the latest update adds ARKit 1.5 for “more immersive augmented reality experiences”. It also adds support for iPhone Battery Health, albeit the Beta. Battery Health displays information on an iPhone’s maximum battery capacity and peak performance capability. “This update also includes stability improvements and bug fixes,” said Apple. The features added in iOS 11.3 are listed below.